<def f='include/boost/asio/basic_socket_acceptor.hpp' l='902' type='endpoint_type boost::asio::basic_socket_acceptor::local_endpoint(boost::system::error_code &amp; ec) const'/>
<doc f='include/boost/asio/basic_socket_acceptor.hpp' l='881'>/**
   * This function is used to obtain the locally bound endpoint of the acceptor.
   *
   * @param ec Set to indicate what error occurred, if any.
   *
   * @returns An object that represents the local endpoint of the acceptor.
   * Returns a default-constructed endpoint object if an error occurred and the
   * error handler did not throw an exception.
   *
   * @par Example
   * @code
   * boost::asio::ip::tcp::acceptor acceptor(io_service);
   * ...
   * boost::system::error_code ec;
   * boost::asio::ip::tcp::endpoint endpoint = acceptor.local_endpoint(ec);
   * if (ec)
   * {
   *   // An error occurred.
   * }
   * @endcode
   */</doc>
